cff-version: 1.2.0
message: "If you use this software, please cite it as below."
title: "QueryBee: a single-file, browser-based fielded Boolean query builder for literature search"
abstract: >-
  A single static HTML file that helps a researcher turn a topic into correctly fielded,
  fully parenthesized Boolean search strings for Scopus, Web of Science, Google Scholar, and
  PubMed. Concept-term expansion (via the user's own AI assistant or by mining the OpenAlex
  literature) is separated from deterministic, per-engine query assembly. No account, API
  key, or server is required.
